ed as such; the public needs to be intensively involved in the processes of risk evaluation and management. Leiss and his collaborators chronicle these organizational risks in a set of detailed case studies on genetically modified foods, cellular telephones, the notorious fuel additive MMT, pulp mill effluent, nuclear power, toxic substances legislation, tobacco, and the new type of "moral risks" associated with genetics technologies such as cloning. Contributors include Debora L. Van Nijnatten (Sir Wilfred Laurier University), Michael D. Mehta (University of Saskatchewan), Stephen Hill (University of Calgary), Éric Darier (Greenpeace), Greg Paoli (Decisionalysis Risk Consultants, Inc.), and Peter V. Hodson (Queen's University).  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aHEALTH & FITNESS / Health Care Issues.2bisacsh1 aDarier, Éric, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHill, Stephen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHodson, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeiss, William, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMehta, Michael D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNijnatten, Debora Van, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPaoli, Greg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077356951540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773569515423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773569515/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  